          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What Exactly Is BugHerd?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "BugHerd is a visual feedback tool that lets your clients and team members report website issues by pointing and clicking directly on a live webpage. Instead of decoding vague emails like \"the button on the right side is broken\" or \"something looks weird near the header,\" you get precise screenshots with exact locations marked.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The tool captures everything automatically: the browser version, screen resolution, operating system, and the exact element someone clicked on. All of this flows into a task board your development team can actually work from.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I started using BugHerd after one too many \"can you fix that thing on the page?\" emails. The difference was immediate. Clients loved how easy it was, and our team stopped wasting hours figuring out what people meant.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
